#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:185
msgid "Tapping"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:188
msgid "Logic for the tap button:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:190
msgid ""
"If only one deck is loaded, the BPM control will be assigned to the loaded "
"deck."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:192
msgid "If both decks are loaded (only 1 PFL ON):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:194
msgid ""
"A. One deck with active PFL, the BPM button will be assigned to the deck "
"with active PFL."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:196
msgid "If both deck is loaded (Both PFL on the same state):"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:198
msgid "A. The BPM button will be assigned to the deck the is playing."
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:200
msgid ""
"B. If both deck are playing, then BPM will control the deck with the lowest "
"deck number"
msgstr ""

#: ../../hardware/controllers/numark_mixtrack_platinum_fx.md:202
msgid ""
"*Note:* *BPM only controls the active deck* *To help know which it is using "
"when tapping BOTH up and down arrows on the deck are lit. As the first tap "
"doesn't make any changes (you can't work out a bpm from one tap) it is safe "
"to tap and hold the button and check which deck the arrows are showing on.*"
msgstr ""

